Ledger Entry 0016
Title: Smart Contract v1 – Deployment Parameters
Date: 2026.01.09.
Repository: corvina-ledger

Summary:
This entry records the fixed deployment parameters
of the Corvina Sigil Jeton (CSJ) smart contract v1.

These parameters define the immutable technical
and governance boundaries of the initial contract
prior to deployment.

────────────────────────────
I. Network Selection
────────────────────────────

Blockchain:
- BNB Chain (Mainnet)

Rationale:
- Low transaction costs
- Mature infrastructure
- Wide wallet compatibility (MetaMask)
- Sufficient decentralization for v1 demonstration

Testnet usage was evaluated but skipped
to reduce operational friction at this stage.
The deployment will be conservative and minimal.

────────────────────────────
II. Token Identity
────────────────────────────

Token Name:
- Corvina Sigil Jeton

Symbol (Ticker):
- CSJ

Decimals:
- 0

Rationale:
- CSJ represents discrete, countable units
- No fractional ownership in v1
- Each jeton corresponds to a clearly defined
  archival, custodial, or intellectual unit

────────────────────────────
III. Total Supply
────────────────────────────

Declared Total Supply:
- 369,000 CSJ

Minting Model:
- Single mint
- One-time execution
- No further minting possible after initial mint

Supply Breakdown:
- Documented in Ledger 0014
- Includes:
  • Physical banknote archive mint
  • Intellectual and standard custody mint

────────────────────────────
IV. Roles and Addresses
────────────────────────────

Founder / Minter Address:
- 0xD248A39081a09Fb8e84c8Dfaa96EB9df7A5a91Ba

Treasury Address:
- 0xC36974d69b18B3f7DB248C82f69F31477beE6Db9

Role Separation:
- Minting authority and treasury custody
  are logically separated
- Distribution is transparent and ledger-tracked

────────────────────────────
V. Contract Controls
────────────────────────────

Pause Function:
- Enabled: Yes
- Scope: Minting only
- Transfers: Always enabled

Ownership:
- Contract ownership initially held
  by Founder address
- Ownership transfer is possible
  but not planned in v1

────────────────────────────
VI. Immutability Guarantees
────────────────────────────

After deployment:
- Token name, symbol, decimals are immutable
- Total supply is fixed
- Mint function is permanently disabled
- Pause affects minting only

Any future changes require:
- New contract version
- Explicit ledger entry
- Public documentation

────────────────────────────
Principles Affirmed:
- Minimal surface area
- No hidden mechanisms
- One-time mint integrity
- Ledger-before-code discipline

Status:
Deployment parameters fixed and approved
for Smart Contract v1 implementation.
